ss=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/payment-processors-how-they-affect-your-business\/#introduction\" title=\"Introduction\">Introduction<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/payment-processors-how-they-affect-your-business\/#what-are-payment-processors\" title=\"What are payment processors?\">What are payment processors?<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/payment-processors-how-they-affect-your-business\/#benefits-of-payment-processors-in-financial-services\" title=\"Benefits of payment processors in financial services\">Benefits of payment processors in financial services<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/payment-processors-how-they-affect-your-business\/#conclusion\" title=\"Conclusion\">Conclusion<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"introduction\"><\/span>Introduction<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The integration of payment processors in any business to allow for payments from contactless means like debit\/credit cards has greatly transformed how things are done in the payments industry. Inasmuch as it has posed some significant challenges for small business, they have greatly changed the game.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, small businesses have the chance to have different transaction data from different sales channels seamlessly flow into one accounting software. Therefore, tasks that were once a bit labour intensive are now automated with minimal errors. This is just one of the benefits of payment processors. Continue reading to learn more.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-are-payment-processors\"><\/span>What are payment processors?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A payment processor is essentially the intermediary between a merchant and the involved financial institutions to ensure that a transaction is successful. Therefore, processors are responsible for managing and authorizing credit card transactions to ensure merchants get paid and customers remain satisfied.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These days businesses don\u2019t have to receive their funds in cash or checks. This is because more and more businesses continue taking their operations online, which means that they are continuously adjusting to the rise of digital payments, and that is where payment processors come in.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These payment processors take the preferred payment method when a customer is checking out and takes it through a series of gateways and approvals. In the end, they either accept or deny the financial transaction in just seconds but for a small fee.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processor-benefits-for-financial-services.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1066\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processor-benefits-for-financial-services.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processor-benefits-for-financial-services-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processor-benefits-for-financial-services-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"benefits-of-payment-processors-in-financial-services\"><\/span>Benefits of payment processors in financial services<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Payment processing for small business entities come with a plethora of benefits. However, many merchants don\u2019t quite comprehend how important these payment processors are in ensuring any online payment is possible. Therefore, here are some of these benefits to help you get a better understanding as to why these processors are important.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>Accepting debit\/credit card payments<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>A payment processor should be capable of processing debit or credit card payments. This might seem a little bit too obvious, but you also have to understand that it may be quite challenging for your business to run without being able to accept card payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having a reliable payment processor is a must for any small business that looks to expand its reach. According to a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.worldpay.com\/us\/insight\/articles\/2018-11\/global-payments-report-2018\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">2018 report<\/a> by Worldpay on global payments, card payments accounted for about 42% of ecommerce payments and about 74% of all the in-store consumer payments in the United States only. This that shows how important contactless payments are why a small business needs to understand the online payment basics.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\"><li><strong>They help businesses offer their customers with alternative payment options<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Customers always want to feel like they have options instead of feeling like they are stuck with one payment method. Inasmuch as debit and credit cards are essential for making payments, they are not the only options in the payment aggregator list. Some great alternatives are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Stripe<br>\u2022 Square<br>\u2022 PayPal<br>\u2022 Braintree<br>\u2022 WorldPay<br>\u2022 Skrill<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, the above options are ideal emerging alternatives that businesses can consider. A payment processor will go a long way in helping <a href=\"https:\/\/www.g2.com\/articles\/e-commerce\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ecommerce businesses<\/a> find the possible mix of ideal alternatives for their customers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It doesn\u2019t matter whether you are in direct links with a payment processor or via third-parties, it would be best to take some time and understand the available alternatives before you choose to commit.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\"><li><strong>It\u2019s a matter of direct pricing and direct relationships<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>There are value-added resellers (VARs) that choose to bundle together payment processing with any other business service. On the other hand, you can find merchant service providers (MSPs) or Independent Sales Organizations (ISOs) that offer pretty much the same service, minus one step from the source.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Such providers just resell the services of payment processors as part of the package. However, today businesses prefer working directly with a payment processor. Such direct relationships are ideal for offering more extensive payments expertise, data security assistance, and superior customer service and fraud protection, among others.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\"><li><strong>Great for integrating payments with your business systems<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The world of business is especially full of specialized systems. That is why they require integrations because they will help these systems communicate, which is vital for ensuring that there is business efficiency while maintaining business sanity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since payments don\u2019t just happen in vacuums, processors function to ensure that they seamlessly integrate with the present business systems like customer relationship management (CRM), billing, accounting and others to ensure efficiency and continuity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"5\"><li><strong>Ensures flexibility to allow for business growth<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Since the payment industry is rapidly evolving, working with a leading payment processor could afford your business the flexibility to grow and stay ahead of the game. This is especially important with the changes taking place in the payment marketplace.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Leading processors will work with a business on every stage, inline third parties that only have the vigor to work with business only in the early stages of growth. These processors will not only grow worth your business but will also be instrumental in helping your business achieve that growth.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-help-business-growth.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1068\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-help-business-growth.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-help-business-growth-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-help-business-growth-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"conclusion\"><\/span>Conclusion<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Integrating a payment processor into your business is not a matter of if but when. It ensures practicality, especially in the post COVID-19 business environment. This is because the customer\u2019s preferences when it comes to payments will always be dynamic and such processors will be ideal in ensuring that you are on the right path. Choosing a payments solution will be great in helping your business soar to great heights.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction The integration of payment processors in any business to allow for payments from contactless means like debit\/credit cards has greatly transformed how things are done in the payments industry. Inasmuch as it has posed some significant challenges for small business, they have greatly changed the game. Today, small businesses have 